A whiteboard lists employers who are scheduling same-day interviews. As students leave, they carry their tote bags while friends relax on the quad, discussing the companies that responded positively to their inquiries.

Tech companies display demo screens showcasing their latest apps, while a robotics startup flies a small drone above its booth for attention, and finance firms provide QR codes for immediate internship applications. Announcement chimes signal the final hour of the fair, and a post-event survey link flashes on the monitors near the exit. Additionally, a startup founder invites students to a lunchtime pitch session. As the event wraps up, volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures. Friends then decompress on the quad, comparing which companies responded warmly.

summaries.120: At a career fair, the staff from the career center log attendance metrics on laptops while event staff scan registrations and distribute lanyards at the entrance. Students rehearse their elevator pitches against the wall, and groups of friends mark target employers on the event map. A data science company showcases a live dashboard providing real-time insights into fair attendance, while tech companies display demo screens for their latest apps. Notably, a robotics startup captures attention by flying a small drone above its booth. Monitors near the exit flash a post-event survey link, and a whiteboard lists employers scheduling same-day interviews. Students use tablets at kiosks to upload resumes to the fair database and compare swag items such as water bottles and phone chargers. Above this scene, a robotics startup flies a small drone above its booth for attention, tech companies display demo screens showing their latest apps, and finance firms offer QR codes for immediate internship applications. Announcement chimes signal the final hour of the fair, and recruiters remind students to follow up with personalized emails. Additionally, an alumni panel discusses how to prepare for technical interviews.

Tech companies display demo screens showcasing their latest apps, while a data science company features a live dashboard of fair attendance. Groups of friends mark target employers on the event map. An alumni panel discusses how to prepare for technical interviews, and alumni volunteers share quick pep talks near the coffee station. Recruiters distribute tote bags filled with branded notebooks and pens and remind students to follow up with personalized emails. A startup founder invites students to a lunchtime pitch session, enhancing networking opportunities. As the day winds down, interview sign-up sheets fill with names, and volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures. Announcement chimes signal the final hour of the fair.

A robotics startup attracts attention by flying a small drone above its booth, while a data science company showcases a live dashboard monitoring fair attendance. Recruiters distribute tote bags filled with branded notebooks and pens. As the event progresses, announcement chimes signal the final hour of the fair, and a post-event survey link flashes on the monitors near the exit. A startup founder invites students to a lunchtime pitch session, and alumni volunteers share quick pep talks near the coffee station. After the fair, volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures.

Tech companies display demo screens featuring their latest apps, while representatives from nonprofits promote mission-driven career paths. A data science company showcases a live dashboard of fair attendance, and announcement chimes signal the final hour of the fair. Groups of friends mark target employers on the event map as they navigate through the opportunities available.
